The paper deals with a communication problem involving noisy observations of a vector Gaussian source, which is a classic problem in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves techniques related to multi-terminal source coding, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The problem of describing a source to a central unit can also be seen as a problem of signal processing, which is covered by cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper involves the evaluation of an outer bound, which is a technique used in optimization and complexity theory, and therefore, it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the rate-distortion region, which is a concept related to data compression, and therefore, it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
